Using a B&W adjustment Layer can also work, but I tried it on different images and the accuracy fluctuates.

Small art tip to check your values in PS

Depending on which method you use, you will get different greyscale results. Here's one that is both quick and accurate:

- Go to Menu -> View -> Proof Setup -> Device to Simulate and pick Working Gray, 20%
- Use Crtl + Y as the shortcut
